modules.description: Provides functions to define commands with customizable completions and associated actions, enabling interactive command-line interfaces. Works with command structures, partial input strings, and completion lists. Used to build REPLs with dynamic tab completion, such as in interactive shells or configuration tools.

Provides functions to execute command-based user interfaces where each command processes an application state and returns a new state. Works with command structures defined as `'a -> 'a Lwt.t` and handles interactive and non-interactive execution flows. Used to display key bindings, generate help messages, and run command sequences from input lines or scripts.
